result.execSummary:
The defendant Natasha Marie Ritter was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Natasha Marie Ritter is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Natasha Marie Ritter was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

1:30 PM District Attorney Halle E. Hatch in Court for State of Wisconsin.  Attorney Liesl E. Nelson in Court with Natasha Marie Ritter.  Ellsworth PD Officer Eric Ladwig in Court.  21CF4 set for Status.  22CF30 set for Motion Hearing.  Court reviews hearing with Court Commissioner, notes that probable cause was not found in Count One.  No findings as to Counts Two-Three.  Atty. Nelson states position that although not explicit, no probable cause found for Counts Two-Three.  Court reviews transcript and believes Motion Hearing should proceed.  Atty. Nelson cites 970.03(10).  Court responds and proceeds w/motion hearing.  DA Hatch states argument and requests Court deny Motion.  Court reviews jury instruction 1909.  Atty. Nelson states argument.  DA Hatch rebuts.  Court makes findings, noting elements.  Not probable cause as to Count Two.  Court dismisses.  Count Three remains.  Court addresses 21CF4.  Court will not revoke the Deferred Judgment agreement.  Court denies State's Motion to Revoke DJOC.
